    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe `diffopt` option `filler` is supposed to add filler lines. `:h diffopt` says this about the `filler` option:\n\n> Show filler lines, to keep the text synchronized with a window that has inserted lines at the same position.  Mostly useful when windows are side-by-side and 'scrollbind' is set.\n\nRemoving the `filler` option with `set diffopt-=filler` does not actually remove the filler lines in diff mode.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. Run `:set diffopt-=filler`\n3. Write into a buffer:\n\n```\nhello\nhi\nhey\n```\n\n3. Create a split window with `:vsplit`\n4. Create a new buffer with `:enew`\n5. Write the following text into the new buffer\n\n```\nhello\nhey\n```\n\n6. Turn on diff mode by calling `:diffthis` from within each window.\n7. You'll see that the filler line is still there.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe buffer with only two lines should not have a filler line appear between the first and second line.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-96e1acfa42 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1767980792\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, vim 9.1.1752 does not have the same issue\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacos 15.7.3\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm 3.6.5\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
